  • Method Details

    • getAllAppointments

      public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<Appointment> getAllAppointments()
      Creates an observablelist of appointments from the appointment database table for the appointment tableview. SELECTs needed data from the table and uses a while loop to extract data from a ResultSet. The observablelist is created one appointment at a time with the appointment constructor.
      Returns:
      all appointments.

    • addAppointment

      public static void addAppointment(String title, String type, String desc, String location, LocalDateTime dtStart, LocalDateTime dtEnd, int customerId, Contact contact)
      INSERTs a new appointment entry into the appointments database table.
      INSERTs user input data and time is converted to a UTC timestamp due to mySQL driver V8.0.X. Creates a localized datetime which is converted to a timestamp for the creation and update time.
      Parameters:
      title - title to set.
      type - type to set.
      desc - description to set.
      location - location to set.
      dtStart - start time to set.
      dtEnd - end time to set.
      customerId - customer ID to set.
      contact - contact to set.

    • modAppointment

      public static void modAppointment(String title, String type, String desc, String location, LocalDateTime dtStart, LocalDateTime dtEnd, int customerId, int uid, Contact contact, int appId)
      Modifies user selected appointment in the appointments database table.
      User input is passed into method and UPDATE is used to modify the data where the Appointment_ID matches the users selection. A LocalDateTime captures the current time when the button is pressed. It is converted to Timestamp to be entered into the table. PreparedStatement is used to pass each value into the corresponding column.
      Parameters:
      title - title update via user input.
      type - type update via user input.
      desc - description update via user input.
      location - location update via user input.
      dtStart - start date and time via user input.
      dtEnd - end date and time via user input.
      customerId - customer ID via user input.
      contact - contact via user input.
      appId - appointment ID via user selection.

    • delAppointment

      public static void delAppointment(Appointment a)
      DELETEs an appointment from the appointments database table (Uses lambda for fewer LoC).
      A confirmation box asks the user if they are sure they want to delete the appointment. If the user selects OK, the appointment is deleted and the user is notified. Confirmation box saves on lines of code and class imports with a lambda expression. If an appointment is deleted, the user is returned to the main view.
      Parameters:
      a - the appointment to delete.

    • checkOverlap

      public static boolean checkOverlap(int customerId, LocalDateTime start, LocalDateTime end)
      Checks the appointment table to time conflicts.
      Finds appointments by Customer_ID and checks for time conflicts. If a conflict is found, the user is notified and the appointment is not created.
      Parameters:
      customerId - customer ID to match for row entry.
      start - start time/date to check.
      end - end time/date to check.
      Returns:
      if a conflict was found or not.

      list of distinct type column entries.
      Throws:
